@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{ato de}}" grammar="@HI{{ato de}}"}}

<body>

<h1>@HI{{ato de}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vta{{}} @EM{{@HI{{ato de}}}}
<li> @N{{}} @HI{{no}} @EM{{@HI{{ato de}}}}
</ol>
</dl>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{ato de}}}} states that the main clause
occurred after the clause preceding the @EM{{@HI{{ato de}}}}.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{attend^matter}}no @EM{{ato de}},@KJ{{drink}}mini @KJ{{going}}kimasenka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Shall we go and have a drink after work?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{new}}shiinowo @KJ{{buy}}tta @EM{{ato de}}, nakushita @KJ{{time^plot}}ga
      @KJ{{see}}tsukarimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      After I bought a new watch I found the old one I'd lost.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
In informal conversations, @HI{{de}} may be dropped.
</p>

<p>
<a href="grammar-te-kara.html">@Vte{{}}@HI{{kara}}</a> has a similar meaning but means "immediately after" whereas @EM{{@HI{{atode}}}}
means "(any time) after".
</p>
 
